    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-20T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-20T23:00:00-05:00" n="440"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-21T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 21, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 21—6:04
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Japanese appear to have made little or no advance since beginning of drive
                        at 7:30 morning of 20th. They are using all forces at their disposal and are
                        apparently burning everything in their path including farmhouses.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>In pronouncements here Japanese are emphasizing the point that they are
                        fighting for the prestige of the West in Asia. In conversation which I had
                        with <persName corresp="#p_MY1">Matsuoka</persName> yesterday he said that
                        Japan would get out of Shanghai “mess” if she could with honor but knew no
                        way out, that she could not afford defeat and in any case could not leave
                        European nations in the lurch by retiring in the face of Chinese
                        force.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
